13:
Teurgis?! You sure you're not a
modded dog?
16:
Okay, jokes aside, did something
happen to Light?
23:
He said he'd only be gone for a bit!
And he wouldn't just ABANDON us.
32:
I've got a pretty good hunch. Follow
me!
36:
I'm fairly sure somebody snatched
Lightâ€”thinking he's a rare mutant.
43:
To us, yeah. But these people think
any animal they haven't seen before
is a mutant.
47:
Okay, but... Light's not exactly an
animal either.
50:
See, mutant battles are prime
entertainment around these parts.
Even a single match involves a lot of
moving credits.
52:
A rare mutant would fetch a hefty
price, since they're always in
demand.
57:
There's a trader in this
neighborhood that's pretty famous.
I've done a few jobs for him, actually.
77:
An electromagnetic cage, huh?
Yeah, that thing will fry you to a crisp.
81:
I'm sorry. I should not have let my
guard down.
85:
Hey, that's enough. Friends look out
for each other, yeah?
88:
I know you'd do the same for us if we
were the ones in the cage.
90:
Hope you're ready to move fast,
because we're not in the clear yet!
96:
Well, well. If it isn't Teurgis. Fancy
seeing you here.
98:
It's a shame a troubleshooter like
you has turned to stealing. If you
needed money, you should've taken
my job offer.
100:
Sorry to disappoint, but Light here is
my friend.
103:
Friend? Don't make me laugh! A
troubleshooter values credits above
honor, doesn't he?
104:
Wait, that's it. My original figure
wasn't enough, was it? How much
do you want?
106:
For a greedy bastard like you, I'll
double the price. Surely that's
satisfactory, Teurgis.
112:
Hey, Alk. How many credits are you
coughing up?
123:
Underestimate a troubleshooter,
and you'll pay for it!
127:
Kicked that job offer to the curb,
then I get saddled with robbery,
assault, and property damage...
130:
Man, this town won't forget about
me anytime soon! Hahaha!
134:
Come hide in Starview. This time,
you're invited.
137: Teurgis, this is all my fault. I am sorry.
140:
Hey now, I said none of that! Besides,
I hated that guy anyways.
142:
I don't do nasty jobs, no matter how
much they pay!
148: You were actually kinda cool today!
151:
Bring on the praise! I'm the world's
number one troubleshooter!
154:
For real though, I might've gone a
little too hard. Could be a long time
before things cool off enough for me
to come back...
155:
In the meantime, I think I'll go look
for work in other worlds.
160:
In Starview, you shall have food and
a warm bed. If there is anything
more you desire, all you need do is
ask.
163:
Thanks for the offer, but honestly, I'd
rather be in debt than be bored!
170:
Maybe started an interstellar
sanctuary? Tried my hand at a little
breeding?
173:
And then, if anyone wanted to see
my beauties, I'd charge them! I'm
gonna be filthy rich!
178:
Why is he looking at me as he says
all that?
181:
Teurgis'll figure out how to survive
anywhere.
185: He is more resilient than a weed...
189:
Yep, got it all figured out! Alk, Light,
it's go time!
